<br>
That night, all of my friends and family gathered in the hospital room.  My wife lay in the bed with him holding him as he occasionally shook and tremored.  We prayed, sincere honest prayer I poured out my soul to God.  My son's great-great grandmother anointed his head with blessed oil from her church.  And you know what?  About 5 minutes later my sons eyes fluttered..he relaxed..opened his eyes..looked at me and said &quot;Daddy..I'm thirsty&quot;.  I wept again.  His neurologist nearly fainted when she saw him the next day..all she could say was &quot;How.....what..how.?&quot;<br>
<br>
My son is about to be 4 years old.  He just learned the pledge of allegiance and The Lord's Prayer.  He's doing exceptionally well in school with no adverse affects.  Not bad for a child that was dead.<br>
<br>
<br>
Tell me there is no God now, I defy you to make me not believe in God. <br>
<br>
If you doubt this..you have only to ask my hotheaded friend and co-worker Trech..he was one of the people in the room when my son opened his eyes.<br>
