Ever gone to holy services?  People don't go to services because they are "insecure" about their faith, and I wouldn't consider scientists insecure for professing their belief in gravity, either.  People go to a church, synagogue, mosque, sacred grove, or other religious space for many reasons.  They go for quiet, for consolation, to worship, to think, etc.  I think the main reason is to share the love and joy they feel in their religion with others, and to receive love and joy in return.  While one doesn't need to go to a sacred space and sing, it is a wonderful feeling to be with others who know G-d exists.<br>
Sorry to post twice in a row, but I had to respond to that.  Also, Poppen, thank you for sharing your story with us.  I have one similar, about a boy I knew from church, my pediatrician's son.  I am so glad your little boy is all right; that is truly the work of G-d.<br>
<br>
