<br>
&quot;Now all those who profess their Faith therefore profess to believe in something that is totally illogical as is CANNOT be proven. No discussion on that one. If you have faith, it CANNOT be logical. Therefore, believing in God, Allah, Yaweh, Satan, Bhudda, or any version thereof is illogical.&quot;<br>
<br>
Incorrect.  Your arguement is not valid, as all you've told us factually is that faith is not based upon proof.  At no point do you give us evidence that faith is inherently at odds with logic.  To put it simply, just because something has not yet been proven does not mean that it cannot be.  You've yet to prove this statement true, or even to give us compelling reason to believe it.<br>
<br>
&quot;God is an alien.&quot;<br>
<br>
Well... yeah.  God certainly qualifies as an extraterrestrial life form, and that makes it an alien.  Granted, god's not some little green man flying around in a spaceship delivering anal probes unto his followers, but I don't think you needed me to tell you that.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
It sort of bothers me how so many people differentiate science and god.  While one can make arguements about the contradiction of science and religion, many people on this thread clearly do not believe that religion = god.  They obviously have something to do with each other, but assuming that they are the same thing is like assuming that a star and a telescope are the same thing.  It's just not true, no matter how many times or how eloquently you argue the point.  God either exists or doesn't exist, and if he exists then he does not do so in opposition to science.  Science is the study of reality, not the study of everything in reality except god.  If we don't understand god yet, or how it works, that's just because science is not advanced enough to do so.  Much like the Earth revolving around the sun, if it's true then it is theoretically possible for science to figure out.  The fact that this hasn't happened yet is irrelevant.<br>
